SOC Investigation

Observed Detection
Alert Title
Registry value entry added to system
Detection Mode
scheduled
Registry Path
HKLM\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\TestService
MITRE ATT&CK
T1112 - Modify Registry
Investigation Findings

Wazuh successfully detected the registry modifications generated during service creation.

The registry entry was associated with the newly created Windows service.

Analysis confirmed that the detected registry path directly matched the service created during the exercise.

Security Impact

If performed by an attacker, this technique could be used to:

Establish Persistence

The service can survive system reboots.

Execute Malicious Code

A service can be configured to launch malware or attacker-controlled programs.

Maintain Elevated Access

Services frequently run with privileged permissions.

Evade Casual Inspection

Background services are often overlooked by users.

