Key Findings
Windows service creation was successfully performed.
Wazuh detected registry modifications related to the service.
Registry path analysis confirmed linkage to the created service.
MITRE ATT&CK technique T1112 was automatically mapped.
Endpoint telemetry collection is functioning correctly.
Lessons Learned
Windows services are a common persistence mechanism.
Service creation results in registry modifications.
Registry monitoring can reveal attacker activity.
Wazuh can detect indirect evidence of attacker actions through system changes.
MITRE ATT&CK mappings help contextualize observed behavior.
